parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery drainage and starting issues can cause the motorcycle to not start, leaving the rider stranded, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: the bike will not start a great deal of the time
the black double arrow bar (fuel pump indicator) is left on the air temp screen
and the bike will not start when there is no bar.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front brake switch can cause the rear brake light to be inoperable, leading to a safety hazard for the rider and other vehicles on the road, as they may not be aware of the rider's braking.
symptoms: The rear brake light is inoperable
the rider must use the foot brake to signal to other vehicles that they are braking

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of metal swarf inside the engine can cause premature wear, rod knock, and engine failure, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
The intermittent power loss and stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially when navigating turns or merging into traffic.
The failure of the throttle position sensor can cause the motorcycle to stutter or surge, leading to loss of control, stalling, or sudden acceleration, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: causing loss of power or sudden acceleration; the idle speed is set inappropriately high (e.g.
1500 RPM); the motorcycle stalls or hesitates when accelerating.
